ğŸ§Š So, the Best Practical â€œSonarQube-Likeâ€ Local Setup
Purpose	Tool	Command
Style / Lint / Speed	ruff	ruff check .
Code Quality / Maintainability	pylint	pylint your_app/
Cognitive Complexity / Maintainability index	radon	radon cc -s -a . and radon mi .
Security Analysis	bandit	bandit -r .
Advanced Pattern / Secure Rules	semgrep	semgrep --config=auto .

This combo yields 95% of SonarQube, without SonarQube.

ğŸ› ï¸ Optional: Run All Automatically (One Script)

Create a script code_quality.sh:

#!/bin/bash
ruff check .
pylint your_app/
radon cc -s -a your_app/
radon mi your_app/
bandit -r your_app/
semgrep --config=auto your_app/


Now just:

bash code_quality.sh

ğŸ¯ Conclusion

If you want one command closest to SonarQube:

pylint your_app/


If you want SonarQube-level deep checks:

ruff + pylint + radon + bandit + semgrep


This is basically industry standard in environments without SonarQube.

